#. <section class="sutta" id="an3.36"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.36:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.36:0.2"
msgid "4. Devadūtavagga"
msgstr "4. Messengers of the Gods"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.36:0.3"
msgid "36. Devadūtasutta"
msgstr "36. Messengers of the Gods"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an3.36:1.1"
msgid "“Tīṇimāni, bhikkhave, devadūtāni."
msgstr "“There are, mendicants, these three messengers of the gods."

msgctxt "an3.36:1.2"
msgid "Katamāni tīṇi?"
msgstr "What three?"

msgctxt "an3.36:1.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco kāyena duccaritaṃ carati, vācāya duccaritaṃ carati, "
"manasā duccaritaṃ carati."
msgstr "Firstly, someone does bad things by way of body, speech, and mind."

msgctxt "an3.36:1.4"
msgid ""
"So kāyena duccaritaṃ caritvā, vācāya duccaritaṃ caritvā, manasā duccaritaṃ "
"caritvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ "
"upapajjati."
msgstr ""
"When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a place of loss, a "
"bad place, the underworld, hell."

msgctxt "an3.36:1.5"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, nirayapālā nānābāhāsu gahetvā yamassa rañño dassenti:"
msgstr ""
"Then the wardens of hell take them by the arms and present them to King "
"Yama, saying:"

msgctxt "an3.36:1.6"
msgid ""
"‘ayaṃ, deva, puriso amatteyyo apetteyyo asāmañño abrahmañño, na kule "
"jeṭṭhāpacāyī."
msgstr ""
"‘Your Majesty, this person did not pay due respect to their mother and "
"father, ascetics and brahmins, or honor the elders in the family."

msgctxt "an3.36:1.7"
msgid "Imassa devo daṇḍaṃ paṇetū’ti."
msgstr "May Your Majesty punish them!’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an3.36:2.1"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, yamo rājā paṭhamaṃ devadūtaṃ samanuyuñjati samanugāhati "
"samanubhāsati:"
msgstr ""
"Then King Yama engages, presses, and examines them about the first messenger "
"of the gods."

msgctxt "an3.36:2.2"
msgid ""
"‘ambho, purisa, na tvaṃ addasa manussesu paṭhamaṃ devadūtaṃ pātubhūtan’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘Mister, did you not see the first messenger of the gods that appeared among "
"human beings?’"

msgctxt "an3.36:2.3"
msgid "So evamāha:"
msgstr "He says:"

msgctxt "an3.36:2.4"
msgid "‘nāddasaṃ, bhante’ti."
msgstr "‘I saw nothing, sir.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an3.36:3.1"
msgid "Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, yamo rājā evamāha:"
msgstr "Then King Yama says:"

#. VAR: daṇḍaparāyaṇaṃ → daṇḍaparāyanaṃ (s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.36:3.2"
msgid ""
"‘ambho purisa, na tvaṃ addasa manussesu itthiṃ vā purisaṃ vā āsītikaṃ vā "
"nāvutikaṃ vā vassasatikaṃ vā jātiyā jiṇṇaṃ gopānasivaṅkaṃ bhoggaṃ "
"daṇḍaparāyaṇaṃ pavedhamānaṃ gacchantaṃ āturaṃ gatayobbanaṃ khaṇḍadantaṃ "
"palitakesaṃ vilūnaṃ khallitasiraṃ valitaṃ tilakāhatagattan’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘Mister, did you not see among human beings an elderly woman or a man—"
"eighty, ninety, or a hundred years old—bent double, crooked, leaning on a "
"staff, trembling as they walk, ailing, past their prime, with teeth broken, "
"hair grey and scanty or bald, skin wrinkled, and limbs blotchy?’"

msgctxt "an3.36:3.3"
msgid "So evamāha:"
msgstr "He says:"

msgctxt "an3.36:3.4"
msgid "‘addasaṃ, bhante’ti."
msgstr "‘I saw that, sir.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.139"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an3.36:4.1"
msgid "Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, yamo rājā evamāha:"
msgstr "Then King Yama says:"

msgctxt "an3.36:4.2"
msgid "‘ambho, purisa, tassa te viññussa sato mahallakassa na etadahosi—"
msgstr "‘Mister, did it not occur to you—being sensible and mature—"

msgctxt "an3.36:4.3"
msgid ""
"ahampi khomhi jarādhammo jaraṃ anatīto, handāhaṃ kalyāṇaṃ karomi, kāyena "
"vācāya manasā’ti?"
msgstr ""
"“I, too, am liable to grow old. I’m not exempt from old age. I’d better do "
"good by way of body, speech, and mind”?’"

msgctxt "an3.36:4.4"
msgid "So evamāha:"
msgstr "He says:"

msgctxt "an3.36:4.5"
msgid "‘nāsakkhissaṃ, bhante. Pamādassaṃ, bhante’ti."
msgstr "‘I couldn’t, sir. I was negligent.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an3.36:5.1"
msgid "Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, yamo rājā evamāha:"
msgstr "Then King Yama says:"

msgctxt "an3.36:5.2"
msgid "‘ambho, purisa, pamādatāya na kalyāṇamakāsi kāyena vācāya manasā."
msgstr ""
"‘Mister, because you were negligent, you didn’t do good by way of body, "
"speech, and mind."

#. VAR: tvaṃ → taṃ (s1-3, mr)
#. VAR: taṃ → te (mr)
msgctxt "an3.36:5.3"
msgid "Taggha tvaṃ, ambho purisa, tathā karissanti yathā taṃ pamattaṃ."
msgstr "Indeed, they’ll definitely punish you to fit your negligence."

#. VAR: Taṃ kho pana te etaṃ → taṃ kho panetaṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
#. VAR: pāpakammaṃ → pāpaṃ kammaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an3.36:5.4"
msgid ""
"Taṃ kho pana te etaṃ pāpakammaṃ neva mātarā kataṃ, na pitarā kataṃ, na "
"bhātarā kataṃ, na bhaginiyā kataṃ, na mittāmaccehi kataṃ, na ñātisālohitehi "
"kataṃ, na devatāhi kataṃ, na samaṇabrāhmaṇehi kataṃ;"
msgstr ""
"That bad deed wasn’t done by your mother, father, brother, or sister. It "
"wasn’t done by friends and colleagues, by relatives and kin, by the deities, "
"or by ascetics and brahmins."

msgctxt "an3.36:5.5"
msgid ""
"atha kho tayāvetaṃ pāpakammaṃ kataṃ, tvaññevetassa vipākaṃ paṭisaṃvedissasī’"
"ti. (1)"
msgstr ""
"That bad deed was done by you alone, and you alone will experience the "
"result.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an3.36:6.1"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, yamo rājā paṭhamaṃ devadūtaṃ samanuyuñjitvā "
"samanugāhitvā samanubhāsitvā, dutiyaṃ devadūtaṃ samanuyuñjati samanugāhati "
"samanubhāsati:"
msgstr "Then King Yama questions them about the second messenger of the gods."

msgctxt "an3.36:6.2"
msgid ""
"‘ambho purisa, na tvaṃ addasa manussesu dutiyaṃ devadūtaṃ pātubhūtan’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘Mister, did you not see the second messenger of the gods that appeared "
"among human beings?’"

msgctxt "an3.36:6.3"
msgid "So evamāha:"
msgstr "He says:"

msgctxt "an3.36:6.4"
msgid "‘nāddasaṃ, bhante’ti."
msgstr "‘I saw nothing, sir.’"

msgctxt "an3.36:6.5"
msgid "Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, yamo rājā evamāha:"
msgstr "Then King Yama says:"

msgctxt "an3.36:6.6"
msgid ""
"‘ambho purisa, na tvaṃ addasa manussesu itthiṃ vā purisaṃ vā ābādhikaṃ "
"dukkhitaṃ bāḷhagilānaṃ, sake muttakarīse palipannaṃ semānaṃ, aññehi "
"vuṭṭhāpiyamānaṃ, aññehi saṃvesiyamānan’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘Mister, did you not see among human beings a woman or a man, sick, "
"suffering, gravely ill, collapsed in their own urine and feces, being picked "
"up by some and put down by others?’"

msgctxt "an3.36:6.7"
msgid "So evamāha:"
msgstr "He says:"

msgctxt "an3.36:6.8"
msgid "‘addasaṃ, bhante’ti."
msgstr "‘I saw that, sir.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an3.36:7.1"
msgid "Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, yamo rājā evamāha:"
msgstr "Then King Yama says:"

msgctxt "an3.36:7.2"
msgid "‘ambho purisa, tassa te viññussa sato mahallakassa na etadahosi:"
msgstr "‘Mister, did it not occur to you—being sensible and mature—"

msgctxt "an3.36:7.3"
msgid ""
"“ahampi khomhi byādhidhammo byādhiṃ anatīto, handāhaṃ kalyāṇaṃ karomi kāyena "
"vācāya manasā”’ti?"
msgstr ""
"“I, too, am liable to become sick. I’m not exempt from sickness. I’d better "
"do good by way of body, speech, and mind”?’"

msgctxt "an3.36:7.4"
msgid "So evamāha:"
msgstr "He says:"

msgctxt "an3.36:7.5"
msgid "‘nāsakkhissaṃ, bhante. Pamādassaṃ, bhante’ti."
msgstr "‘I couldn’t, sir. I was negligent.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.140"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an3.36:8.1"
msgid "Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, yamo rājā evamāha:"
msgstr "Then King Yama says:"

msgctxt "an3.36:8.2"
msgid "‘ambho purisa, pamādatāya na kalyāṇamakāsi kāyena vācāya manasā."
msgstr ""
"‘Mister, because you were negligent, you didn’t do good by way of body, "
"speech, and mind."

msgctxt "an3.36:8.3"
msgid "Taggha tvaṃ, ambho purisa, tathā karissanti yathā taṃ pamattaṃ."
msgstr "Well, they’ll definitely punish you to fit your negligence."

msgctxt "an3.36:8.4"
msgid ""
"Taṃ kho pana te etaṃ pāpakammaṃ neva mātarā kataṃ, na pitarā kataṃ, na "
"bhātarā kataṃ, na bhaginiyā kataṃ, na mittāmaccehi kataṃ, na ñātisālohitehi "
"kataṃ, na devatāhi kataṃ, na samaṇabrāhmaṇehi kataṃ;"
msgstr ""
"That bad deed wasn’t done by your mother, father, brother, or sister. It "
"wasn’t done by friends and colleagues, by relatives and kin, by the deities, "
"or by ascetics and brahmins."

msgctxt "an3.36:8.5"
msgid ""
"atha kho tayāvetaṃ pāpakammaṃ kataṃ. Tvaññevetassa vipākaṃ paṭisaṃvedissasī’"
"ti. (2)"
msgstr ""
"That bad deed was done by you alone, and you alone will experience the "
"result.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "an3.36:9.1"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, yamo rājā dutiyaṃ devadūtaṃ samanuyuñjitvā samanugāhitvā "
"samanubhāsitvā, tatiyaṃ devadūtaṃ samanuyuñjati samanugāhati samanubhāsati:"
msgstr "Then King Yama questions them about the third messenger of the gods."

msgctxt "an3.36:9.2"
msgid ""
"‘ambho purisa, na tvaṃ addasa manussesu tatiyaṃ devadūtaṃ pātubhūtan’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘Mister, did you not see the third messenger of the gods that appeared among "
"human beings?’"

msgctxt "an3.36:9.3"
msgid "So evamāha:"
msgstr "He says:"

msgctxt "an3.36:9.4"
msgid "‘nāddasaṃ, bhante’ti."
msgstr "‘I saw nothing, sir.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "an3.36:10.1"
msgid "Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, yamo rājā evamāha:"
msgstr "Then King Yama says:"

msgctxt "an3.36:10.2"
msgid ""
"‘ambho purisa, na tvaṃ addasa manussesu itthiṃ vā purisaṃ vā ekāhamataṃ vā "
"dvīhamataṃ vā tīhamataṃ vā uddhumātakaṃ vinīlakaṃ vipubbakajātan’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘Mister, did you not see among human beings a woman or a man, dead for one, "
"two, or three days, bloated, livid, and festering?’"

msgctxt "an3.36:10.3"
msgid "So evamāha:"
msgstr "He says,"

msgctxt "an3.36:10.4"
msgid "‘addasaṃ, bhante’ti."
msgstr "‘I saw that, sir.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "an3.36:11.1"
msgid "Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, yamo rājā evamāha:"
msgstr "Then King Yama says:"

msgctxt "an3.36:11.2"
msgid "‘ambho purisa, tassa te viññussa sato mahallakassa na etadahosi—"
msgstr "‘Mister, did it not occur to you—being sensible and mature—"

msgctxt "an3.36:11.3"
msgid ""
"ahampi khomhi maraṇadhammo maraṇaṃ anatīto, handāhaṃ kalyāṇaṃ karomi kāyena "
"vācāya manasā’ti?"
msgstr ""
"“I, too, am liable to die. I’m not exempt from death. I’d better do good by "
"way of body, speech, and mind”?’"

msgctxt "an3.36:11.4"
msgid "So evamāha:"
msgstr "He says:"

msgctxt "an3.36:11.5"
msgid "‘nāsakkhissaṃ, bhante. Pamādassaṃ, bhante’ti."
msgstr "‘I couldn’t, sir. I was negligent.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "an3.36:12.1"
msgid "Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, yamo rājā evamāha:"
msgstr "Then King Yama says:"

msgctxt "an3.36:12.2"
msgid "‘ambho purisa, pamādatāya na kalyāṇamakāsi kāyena vācāya manasā."
msgstr ""
"‘Mister, because you were negligent, you didn’t do good by way of body, "
"speech, and mind."

msgctxt "an3.36:12.3"
msgid "Taggha tvaṃ, ambho purisa, tathā karissanti yathā taṃ pamattaṃ."
msgstr "Well, they’ll definitely punish you to fit your negligence."

msgctxt "an3.36:12.4"
msgid ""
"Taṃ kho pana te etaṃ pāpakammaṃ neva mātarā kataṃ, na pitarā kataṃ, na "
"bhātarā kataṃ, na bhaginiyā kataṃ, na mittāmaccehi kataṃ, na ñātisālohitehi "
"kataṃ, na devatāhi kataṃ, na samaṇabrāhmaṇehi kataṃ;"
msgstr ""
"That bad deed wasn’t done by your mother, father, brother, or sister. It "
"wasn’t done by friends and colleagues, by relatives and kin, by the deities, "
"or by ascetics and brahmins."

msgctxt "an3.36:12.5"
msgid ""
"atha kho tayāvetaṃ pāpakammaṃ kataṃ. Tvaññevetassa vipākaṃ paṭisaṃvedissasī’”"
"ti. (3)"
msgstr ""
"That bad deed was done by you alone, and you alone will experience the "
"result.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.141"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "an3.36:13.1"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, yamo rājā tatiyaṃ devadūtaṃ samanuyuñjitvā samanugāhitvā "
"samanubhāsitvā tuṇhī hoti."
msgstr ""
"Then, after questioning them about the third messenger of the gods, King "
"Yama falls silent."

msgctxt "an3.36:13.2"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, nirayapālā pañcavidhabandhanaṃ nāma kāraṇaṃ karonti."
msgstr "Then the wardens of hell punish them with the five-fold crucifixion."

msgctxt "an3.36:13.3"
msgid ""
"Tattaṃ ayokhilaṃ hatthe gamenti. Tattaṃ ayokhilaṃ dutiyasmiṃ hatthe gamenti. "
"Tattaṃ ayokhilaṃ pāde gamenti. Tattaṃ ayokhilaṃ dutiyasmiṃ pāde gamenti. "
"Tattaṃ ayokhilaṃ majjhe urasmiṃ gamenti."
msgstr ""
"They drive red-hot stakes through the hands and feet, and another in the "
"middle of the chest."

#. VAR: tibbā → tippā (bj)
msgctxt "an3.36:13.4"
msgid ""
"So tattha dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vediyati, na ca tāva kālaṃ karoti "
"yāva na taṃ pāpakammaṃ byantīhoti."
msgstr ""
"And there they feel painful, intense, severe, acute feelings—but they don’t "
"die until that bad deed is eliminated."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
#. VAR: saṃvesetvā → saṃvesitvā (s1-3, pts1) | saṃkaḍḍhitvā (mr)
msgctxt "an3.36:14.1"
msgid "Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, nirayapālā saṃvesetvā kudhārīhi tacchanti."
msgstr "Then the wardens of hell thrown them down and hack them with axes. …"

msgctxt "an3.36:14.2"
msgid ""
"So tattha dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vediyati, na ca tāva kālaṃ karoti "
"yāva na taṃ pāpakammaṃ byantīhoti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
#. VAR: uddhampādaṃ → uddhapādaṃ (bj)
#. VAR: gahetvā → ṭhapetvā (bj, s1-3)
msgctxt "an3.36:15.1"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, nirayapālā uddhampādaṃ adhosiraṃ gahetvā vāsīhi "
"tacchanti … pe …"
msgstr "They hang them upside-down and hack them with hatchets. …"

#. VAR: sajotibhūtāya → sañjotibhūtāya (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "an3.36:15.2"
msgid ""
"tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, nirayapālā rathe yojetvā ādittāya bhūmiyā sampajjalitāya "
"sajotibhūtāya sārentipi paccāsārentipi … pe …"
msgstr ""
"They harness them to a chariot, and drive them back and forth across burning "
"ground, blazing and glowing. …"

msgctxt "an3.36:15.3"
msgid ""
"tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, nirayapālā mahantaṃ aṅgārapabbataṃ ādittaṃ sampajjalitaṃ "
"sajotibhūtaṃ āropentipi oropentipi … pe …"
msgstr ""
"They make him climb up and down a huge mountain of burning coals, blazing "
"and glowing. …"

#. VAR: () → (so tattha pheṇuddehakaṃ paccati) (bj) | (so tattha phenuddehakaṃ paccati) (s1-3)
msgctxt "an3.36:15.4"
msgid ""
"tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, nirayapālā uddhampādaṃ adhosiraṃ gahetvā tattāya "
"lohakumbhiyā pakkhipanti, ādittāya sampajjalitāya sajotibhūtāya. ()"
msgstr ""
"Then the wardens of hell turn them upside down and throw them in a red-hot "
"copper pot, burning, blazing, and glowing."

msgctxt "an3.36:15.5"
msgid ""
"So tattha pheṇuddehakaṃ paccamāno sakimpi uddhaṃ gacchati, sakimpi adho "
"gacchati, sakimpi tiriyaṃ gacchati."
msgstr ""
"There they’re seared in boiling scum, and they’re swept up and down and "
"round and round."

msgctxt "an3.36:15.6"
msgid ""
"So tattha dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vediyati, na ca tāva kālaṃ karoti "
"yāva na taṃ pāpakammaṃ byantīhoti."
msgstr ""
"And there they feel painful, intense, severe, acute feelings—but they don’t "
"die until that bad deed is eliminated."

msgctxt "an3.36:15.7"
msgid "Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, nirayapālā mahāniraye pakkhipanti."
msgstr "Then the wardens of hell toss them into the Great Hell."

msgctxt "an3.36:15.8"
msgid "So kho pana, bhikkhave, mahānirayo—"
msgstr "Now, about that Great Hell:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "an3.36:16.1"
msgid "Catukkaṇṇo catudvāro,"
msgstr "‘Four are its corners, four its doors,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.36:16.2"
msgid "vibhatto bhāgaso mito;"
msgstr "divided into measured parts."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.36:16.3"
msgid "Ayopākārapariyanto,"
msgstr "Surrounded by an iron wall,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.36:16.4"
msgid "ayasā paṭikujjito."
msgstr "of iron is its roof."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.142"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc17"></a>
msgctxt "an3.36:17.1"
msgid "Tassa ayomayā bhūmi,"
msgstr "The ground is even made of iron,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.36:17.2"
msgid "Jalitā tejasā yutā;"
msgstr "it burns with fierce fire."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.36:17.3"
msgid "Samantā yojanasataṃ,"
msgstr "The heat forever radiates"

# Note: BB translates as if the hell itself covers 100 leagues, but usually to “pharati” is to “pervade” with some radiation, such a metta, etc. Here I think it means that the heat of the Great Hell pervades the surrounding regions.
#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.36:17.4"
msgid "Pharitvā tiṭṭhati sabbadāti."
msgstr "a hundred leagues around.’"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc18"></a>
msgctxt "an3.36:18.1"
msgid "Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, yamassa rañño etadahosi:"
msgstr "Once upon a time, King Yama thought:"

msgctxt "an3.36:18.2"
msgid ""
"‘ye kira, bho, loke pāpakāni kammāni karonti te evarūpā vividhā kammakāraṇā "
"karīyanti."
msgstr ""
"‘Those who do such bad deeds in the world receive these many different "
"punishments."

msgctxt "an3.36:18.3"
msgid ""
"Aho vatāhaṃ manussattaṃ labheyyaṃ, tathāgato ca loke uppajjeyya arahaṃ "
"sammāsambuddho, tañcāhaṃ bhagavantaṃ payirupāseyyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Oh, I hope I may be reborn as a human being! And that a Realized One—a "
"perfected one, a fully awakened Buddha—arises in the world! And that I may "
"pay homage to the Buddha!"

msgctxt "an3.36:18.4"
msgid ""
"So ca me bhagavā dhammaṃ deseyya, tassa cāhaṃ bhagavato dhammaṃ ājāneyyan’ti."
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha can teach me Dhamma, so that I may understand his teaching.’"

msgctxt "an3.36:18.5"
msgid ""
"Taṃ kho panāhaṃ, bhikkhave, na aññassa samaṇassa vā brāhmaṇassa vā sutvā "
"evaṃ vadāmi, api ca kho, bhikkhave, yadeva me sāmaṃ ñātaṃ sāmaṃ diṭṭhaṃ "
"sāmaṃ viditaṃ tadevāhaṃ vadāmīti."
msgstr ""
"Now, I don’t say this because I’ve heard it from some other ascetic or "
"brahmin. I only say it because I’ve known, seen, and realized it for myself.”"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc19"></a>
msgctxt "an3.36:19.1"
msgid "Coditā devadūtehi,"
msgstr "“Those people who are negligent,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.36:19.2"
msgid "ye pamajjanti māṇavā;"
msgstr "when warned by the gods’ messengers:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.36:19.3"
msgid "Te dīgharattaṃ socanti,"
msgstr "a long time they sorrow,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.36:19.4"
msgid "hīnakāyūpagā narā."
msgstr "when they go to that wretched place."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc20"></a>
msgctxt "an3.36:20.1"
msgid "Ye ca kho devadūtehi,"
msgstr "But those good and peaceful people,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.36:20.2"
msgid "santo sappurisā idha;"
msgstr "when warned by the god’s messengers,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.36:20.3"
msgid "Coditā nappamajjanti,"
msgstr "never neglect"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.36:20.4"
msgid "ariyadhamme kudācanaṃ."
msgstr "the noble teaching."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc21"></a>
msgctxt "an3.36:21.1"
msgid "Upādāne bhayaṃ disvā,"
msgstr "Seeing the peril in grasping,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.36:21.2"
msgid "jātimaraṇasambhave;"
msgstr "the origin of birth and death,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.36:21.3"
msgid "Anupādā vimuccanti,"
msgstr "they’re freed by not grasping,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.36:21.4"
msgid "jātimaraṇasaṅkhaye."
msgstr "with the ending of birth and death."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc22"></a>
#. VAR: appamattā → te khoppattā (bj) | te khemappattā (s1-3, km, pts1)
#. VAR: sukhino → sukhitā (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.36:22.1"
msgid "Te appamattā sukhino,"
msgstr "Happy, they’ve come to a safe place,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.36:22.2"
msgid "diṭṭhadhammābhinibbutā;"
msgstr "extinguished in this very life."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.36:22.3"
msgid "Sabbaverabhayātītā,"
msgstr "They’ve gone beyond all threats and perils,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.36:22.4"
msgid "sabbadukkhaṃ upaccagun”ti."
msgstr "and risen above all suffering.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.36:22.5"
msgid "Chaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr ""
